### 1.2 CouchDB → PostgreSQL Event Projection Pipeline

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant PDB as PouchDB (Device)
    participant COUCH as CouchDB
    participant PROJ as Change Feed Projector<br/>(Node.js worker)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL

    PDB->>COUCH: Sync writes
    COUCH->>PROJ: _changes feed (live)
    PROJ->>PROJ: Transform doc → relational rows
    PROJ->>PG: INSERT/UPDATE into tables

    Note over PG: Optimized tables:<br/>orders, line_items, payments,<br/>daily_sales, tax_report,<br/>inventory_movements
```

**PostgreSQL Tables (projection targets):**

| PG Table | Source Doc | Purpose |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| `pg_orders` | `order:*` | Flat order records for queries |
| `pg_order_line_items` | `order:*.items[]` | Denormalized line items |
| `pg_payments` | `order:*.payments[]` | Payment records, Razorpay IDs |
| `pg_tax_summary` | `order:*.tax_breakdown[]` | CGST/SGST/IGST aggregation |
| `pg_daily_sales` | Aggregated | Daily revenue by outlet |
| `pg_inventory_movements` | `inv:*` changes | Stock in/out log |
| `pg_webhook_events` | Razorpay webhooks | Idempotency store |
| `pg_party_state` | `party:*` | Soundbox state machine lookups |

### 1.3 Sync & Conflict Resolution

| Document Type | Strategy | Rationale |
|---------------|----------|-----------|
| `order` (line items) | **Semantic merge** — union of `items[]`, dedup by `line_id` | Two waiters adding items concurrently |
| `order` (status) | **Last-write-wins** with `updated_at` | Status transitions are sequential |
| `party` | **Server-wins** for `payment_*` fields; **LWW** for `status` | Webhook payment state is authoritative |
| `table` | **Last-write-wins** | Single device per table typically |
| `inventory` (stock) | **CRDT delta merge** — store deltas, not absolutes | Concurrent sales shouldn't lose deductions |
| `item` / `category` | **Last-write-wins** | Admin edits are infrequent |

