## WS2: Frontend POS UI

### 2.1 Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| Build | **Vite 6** | Clean static output for Capacitor `file://` |
| Framework | **React 19** | Component ecosystem, hooks |
| Routing | **React Router 7** (hash mode) | Avoids `file://` history API issues |
| State | **Zustand** | Lightweight, offline-compatible |
| DB Layer | **PouchDB + `useLiveQuery` hooks** | Reactive UI from local DB |
| PWA | **Serwist** (vite-plugin) | Service worker + precaching |
| Styling | **Vanilla CSS + Custom Properties** | Brand design tokens |
| Fonts | **Outfit + Inter** (Google Fonts, self-hosted) | Offline availability |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **React Router must use hash-based routing** (`createHashRouter`) inside Capacitor. The `file://` scheme does not support `pushState`/`popstate` correctly on all Android WebView versions. This is a known Capacitor caveat.

