## Structural Risks & Mitigations

| # | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|------|----------|------------|
| R1 | **PouchDB + Vite ESM bundling:** PouchDB has legacy CommonJS internals and Node.js polyfill dependencies (`events`, `buffer`). Vite's ESM-first bundler may fail to resolve them without explicit configuration. | 🔴 High | Add `optimizeDeps.include: ['pouchdb', 'pouchdb-find']` in `vite.config.ts`. Use `vite-plugin-node-polyfills` for `buffer` and `events`. Pin PouchDB to a version known to work with Vite 6. Test build early. |
| R2 | **Hash routing + deep links:** The Digital Menu app uses path-based routing for SEO (QR code links like `menu.skillsetgo.com/OUT001`), but the POS app uses hash routing. Two different routing modes in the same monorepo. | 🟡 Medium | They're separate Vite apps with separate `vite.config.ts`. Digital Menu uses `createBrowserRouter`; POS uses `createHashRouter`. No conflict, but developers must be aware of the distinction. |
| R3 | **CouchDB→PG projector lag:** Under high write volume (busy dinner service), the change feed projector may fall behind, causing stale reports. | 🟡 Medium | The projector runs as a dedicated Node.js worker with `_changes?feed=continuous&heartbeat=10000`. Add a `seq` checkpoint to resume from last-processed change. Monitor lag with a heartbeat metric. Reports page shows "Last synced: X minutes ago" indicator. |
| R4 | **Android TTS voice quality varies by OEM:** Samsung, Xiaomi, and stock Android ship different TTS engines (Google TTS, Samsung TTS, etc.) with varying quality and language support. | 🟡 Medium | On app start, call `getAvailableLanguages()` and fall back to `en-US` if requested locale unavailable. Recommend installing Google TTS engine via Settings prompt if quality is poor. Log TTS engine name for debugging. |
| R5 | **Foreground Service killed by aggressive OEMs:** Xiaomi MIUI, Samsung OneUI, and Oppo ColorOS aggressively kill background services even with `START_STICKY`. | 🟡 Medium | Use `WakeLock`, proper notification channel, and `START_STICKY`. Add in-app guide: "Disable battery optimization for SkillSetGo POS in Settings → Apps." Test on Xiaomi and Samsung specifically during QA. |
| R6 | **IndexedDB storage quota on Android WebView:** Android WebView grants ~100-200MB per origin (varies by OS version). A busy restaurant could exceed this in weeks. | 🟡 Medium | Implement auto-archival: closed orders older than 30 days are purged from PouchDB (they persist in CouchDB + PostgreSQL). Run `db.compact()` weekly. Monitor storage via `navigator.storage.estimate()`. |
| R7 | **PouchDB conflict storms on multi-device busy nights:** Two tablets editing the same order doc simultaneously creates revision branches. | 🟡 Medium | V1 mitigation: granular docs (each order is one doc, but `line_id` dedup prevents item loss). V2 consideration: split to 1 doc per line item for true conflict-free concurrent editing. |
| R8 | **Google Fonts offline availability:** If fonts are loaded from Google CDN, they fail offline on first visit. | 🟢 Low | Self-host variable font files in `public/fonts/`. Use `@font-face` declarations in `typography.css` instead of CDN `@import`. Already planned in the file layout above. |
| R9 | **Razorpay webhook delivery failure:** Razorpay retries with exponential backoff, but if the server is down for extended periods, webhooks may be exhausted. | 🟡 Medium | Implement a polling fallback: a cron job runs every 5 minutes, fetches recent Razorpay orders via API, and reconciles against `pg_webhook_events`. |
| R10 | **Offline bill number collisions across devices:** Two tablets generate `SSG-DEV01-00042` simultaneously if they share a device code. | 🟡 Medium | Each tablet has a unique `DeviceDoc` with its own `device_code` (DEV01, DEV02, etc.) and independent `bill_counter`. Collision is impossible because the prefix differs. Server-side dedup on sync as safety net. |

